From the above, we see the contents of toukmond's home directory. It has some
apparent executables, such as 'cd' and 'cat'. Although they are the right size,
they are not actual executables. Their purpose in the game is to let the player
know the limited number of commands available. And you only need to implement
these: cd, pwd, ls, cat, uncompress. Also, you do not need to implement things
that the game cannot do, like cat /rooms/mailroom/description.

We also see that paper.o.gz is actually zipped (.gz) not compressed (.Z). This
does not mean that your game won't say paper.o.Z; it only means your fake ls
needs to change how the zipped file displays, and it also means that you will
use gunzip in your implementation of the fake uncompress.


