What does it all mean? It means that your fake ls implementation has
to have the right wildcard pattern to match all of the things that
it should match to (eg, description, shovel.o, uncompress, etc), and
none of the things that it shouldn't match to (eg, trees, e, etc.).
And this wildcard pattern should work for all the directories in
pokey, not just this one.


